node.text:
Fatherhood has a different definition for everyone. Sometimes that definition is beautiful and filled with love. Sometimes it’s complicated and difficult to explain. Other times the definition is flat out painful. 

Today I’m grateful that my dad gave me an incredible, sacrificial, loving, generous, hilarious, loyal, and kind definition of fatherhood. I know for sure that he’s given me the very best that he has. Not only was your best good enough daddy, it was more than enough. 

I could spend the rest of my life living and sharing what you’ve poured into me and it will still never fully measure up to how much wisdom, strength, love, and character you’ve given me. 
My cup overflows. Happy Father’s Day  Daddy! I love you so much. 

May this prayer reach every heart who needs it the most.

node.title: My dad @bishopjakes is why I define fatherhood as covering.

node.text:
I truly believe the greatest gift we can give our mothers is to reflect back to them the greatest parts of who they are. 

I am filled with the essence of Serita Jakes and I reflect her with me everywhere I go. All I’ve ever done is spoken the words she’d say to me back to her. 

She has shown me what it means to be honest, vulnerable, powerful, hilarious, classy, and kind. She’s shown me what God can do with pieces. 
 
Today I speak her name because I believe her when she said she’s as close to me as the mention of her name even though we’re miles apart. 

Mom, mom, mom, mom, mom..... I miss you.  I love you. You’re my definition, my optimism, my hallelujah, my angel. You are my queen, my friend, my sister. I live in the span of your wings. I call it home.
You are pure love embodied with sass.  I love every bit of you! 

Happy Mother’s Day to every mother whose given it her all. Special love to those who carry a twinge of pain on today. May God’s presence cover your wounds and reveal joy even in the middle of the pain.

node.text:
Siblings are overrated in youth and underrated in adulthood. When you’re growing up they’re a forced BFF that steals your clothing, friends, and do a LOT of snitching. When you become adults they wipe your tears, celebrate your wins, and do a lot of snickering. 

Cora you are my girl. I love you so very much. I am convinced that your DNA is made up of love, laughter, kindness, and sassy. You’d think that us not living in the same state would make it challenging for our children to be close, but a heart like yours cannot be restricted by distance. 

I feel so blessed that my family has you in our village. We are better, wiser, stronger, and happier because of it. I’m wishing you more of you for your birthday. May you have divine encounters with the highest version of who God has called you to be. May it take you by surprise and change the way you show up in this world. 

You are my forever my girl. I will forever cheer you on. My love for you will never end. Happy Birthday my Queen Sister!

node.text:
Today I turned 33, which is apparently old enough to be some folks’ auntie. I’ve lived a lot of life for someone my age. That’s always made me feel heavy emotionally, spiritually, and mentally. 

This month I’ve tried to be intentional about relieving myself of some pressures and responsibilities so that I could be present in my life. 

One thing that has risen to the surface is gratitude. I’m so grateful to be alive. If you’re reading this we’ve walked through the valley of the shadow of death during this pandemic. We’re still here. 
 
I used to take tomorrow for granted but the trauma of the unexpected has taught me to soak in every moment. I chose to soak your love in today. I allowed it to fill me up. I count you as God’s gift to my soul. 

Thank you for taking time out of your day to celebrate me. Every comment, story, and post was a drop in my cup. Thank you for pouring in to me. 

BTW….@toureroberts been macking me down like he wants to marry me and I think it’s going to work. Thank you baby for an incredible love and a remarkable birthday. You are my king for real.

node.text:
What does it look like to trust God? It means letting go of your need to have the outcome you desire and saying, “God, I’ll have peace wherever this journey takes me.” 

Sometimes we utter these words with confidence. Sometimes we utter these words with fear. The power is in the surrender.

node.text:
My book, Woman Evolve, came out 4/6 and in May it reached this incredible milestone. I wish I could say that it was a result of savvy strategy, but I know that wouldn’t be entirely true. 

Woman Evolve has reached so many women because thousands of men and women wanted to make sure no woman in their sphere was left behind. 

No matter where we are in life there’s an opportunity for us to discover God’s strategy for our present. If you are a woman (or know a woman) who could use a reminder that it’s never too late to revolutionize her life please get her this book. 

Click the link in my bio and get plugged in to a book club community just for Woman Evolve. 

#nowomanleftbehind #womanevolve #sarahjakesroberts
